 state organized by the White Croats in a part of Central Europe that\
 can not be conclusively identified today. The main source of the\
 existence of a White Croatian state is a mention by the Byzantine\
 Emperor Constantine VII Porphyrogennetos. White Croatia is sometimes\
 associated with a prince Slavnik, lord of Libice, whose influence\
 extended to the region of Silesia and the land of Krakow.")

