 The British West Indies formed the short-lived West Indies Federation in\
 1958. The federation failed to consolidate because of tensions between\
 Trinidad, Jamaica and the smaller members. The federation fell apart in\
 1962. Some islands became independent countries, others returned to\
 the status of a British dependency.")

